{"id":539,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":539,"title":"Giants","subtitle":"","short_title":"Giants","uri":"/scriptures/bd/giants","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/giants.t1","order":".000.1408"},[".title","Giants"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/giants.p1","order":".000.1409"},"Unusually large, tall persons, apparently having great physical strength. They are mentioned both before the Flood (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/6.4"},"Gen. 6:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/8.18"},"Moses 8:18"],") and after (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/13.33"},"Num. 13:33"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/2.10-11,20"},"Deut. 2:10–11, 20"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/3.11-13"},"3:11–13"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/9.2"},"9:2"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/15.8"},"Josh. 15:8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/18.16"},"18:16"],"). Raphah of Gath was said to be the father of several giants of whom Goliath was one (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/17.4-7"},"1 Sam. 17:4–7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/21.16-22"},"2 Sam. 21:16–22"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/20.6"},"1 Chr. 20:6"],"). A 12-fingered, 12-toed giant is also mentioned as one of the sons. The giants in Palestine were also known as Anakims, Emims, and Zamzummims."]]],"refs":null}
